There will be no additional tests for seniors.
Why?
According to Rafał Trzaskowski's announcements, a program of free preventive examinations for seniors aged 70 and 80 was to be introduced in Warsaw.
However, the idea will not be implemented because it has not been approved by the Ministry of Health and its subordinate Agency for the Protection of Health Technology and Tariffication.
In the justification, the agency explained that the target group was poorly selected.
"The above actions may even result in the detection of individual disease entities, which may contribute to the deepening of difficulties in accessing NFZ services and negatively affect the patient, causing anxiety and discomfort associated with a false positive test result," it was written.
The decision of the ministry is not understood by the president of the capital.
"The money is ours, we have the money for it.
