Make sure you're washing your hands well
We all know that they need to be washed (e.g. after coming home or before a meal).
But not everyone knows that in order to actually get rid of germs, you need to do it in the right way.
This is especially important now that autumn infections are approaching.
It takes at least 30-40 seconds for washing to sufficiently remove dangerous bacteria and viruses from our hands
And yet most of us wash them shorter!
All you need is warm water and ordinary soap – it is not true that it must be antibacterial (many doctors even advise against it).
When washing, rub not only the bottoms and tops of the hand, but also: the tips of the fingers (joined or individually) – rub them with circular movements on the inside of the other hand, the spaces between the fingers (interlace your hands, rubbing your fingers against each other), thumbs – each thumb is covered with the other hand and in such an embrace we turn it for a moment to the right and left.
In an emergency situation (when you can not wash your hands) you should wipe your hands with a wet handkerchief, and then use antibacterial gel (in drugstores, from PLN 5).
After using the public toilet, do not touch the handles or doors with washed hands (recommendation of the Chief Sanitary Inspectorate).
Open them with a paper towel.
Iran's president says he has rejected the offer of talks with the US, Donald Trump denies
Tehran has not held talks with the U.S. side at the U.N. General Assembly in New York, despite an offer by the U.S. to lift sanctions, Iranian President Hassan Rouhani said on Friday.
U.S. President Donald Trump commented that it was the Iranian side that asked for the lifting of restrictions, which he did not agree to.
According to Iranian President Hassan Rouhani, the Americans offered to lift all sanctions imposed on Tehran in exchange for negotiations on a new international agreement.
It would regulate both Iran's nuclear and ballistic missile programs.
Rouhani: Iran will not hold talks under maximum pressure
Iran's president said he had refused to hold the talks because of the "toxic atmosphere."
He stated that he met with American diplomats because he had succumbed to the persuasion of France, Germany and Great Britain.
He stressed, however, that Iran would not enter into talks in an atmosphere of "maximum pressure".
"And even if we want to negotiate with the Americans in the 5+1 format, no one can predict what the end result will be," Rouhani said.
A day earlier, the Iranian leader said that he did not rule out talks with the US, and accused the European parties to the nuclear deal of supporting US sanctions on Iran.
He added that sanctions imposed on Iran after the U.S. withdrawal from the nuclear deal "are a precondition that does not allow" for dialogue.
If we can lift this precondition and if America lifts sanctions and maximum pressure, then of course we can talk to America.
He added that he did not rule out a meeting with US President Donald Trump, despite the fact that he did not agree to such a conversation last week during the UN General Assembly.
Trump: 'Iran Asked, I Said No'
Donald Trump wrote on Twitter that it was he who rejected the request of the Iranian side.
"Iran wanted me to lift the sanctions imposed on them so that we could meet.
Of course I said 'no!'" tweeted the US president.
Tension with nuclear agreement in the background
France, Germany and Britain are trying to ease tensions between Washington and Tehran in some form to save the 2015 Iran deal to which they were signatories.
It stipulated that in exchange for the lifting of economic sanctions, Iran would give up its nuclear weapons program and bring the nuclear sector under the control of the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA).
Since the U.S. withdrew from the agreement in May 2015, the other signatories have repeatedly confirmed that they want to keep the agreement in force.
So far, nothing has come of it.
Washington is using the tactic of exerting maximum pressure on Iran, and the sanctions also include a full embargo on Iranian oil.
Tehran has announced that if it does not receive permission to export raw material, it will reduce its obligations under the agreement every 60 days.
