The competition of the power of jumping consists in overcoming by the rider and horse higher and higher obstacles, which in the most prestigious international competitions exceed even two meters.
It is worth adding here that the long-standing and still unbeaten world record, set back in 1949 by the Chilean Albert Larraguibel, on the horse "Huaso", is 247 cm.
Of course, no one jumped so high in Oława, but the result of the best local amazons at the level of 135 cm is not the worst either...
The competition organized by the tireless Jan Sienkiewicz and other JKS activists "In the saddle" was a demonstration part of the "Rainbow Equestrian Competition" held there a little earlier, about which we write in more detail in this issue of the newspaper, on page 22.
Eight Amazons joined the competition, training horse riding in the Oława JKS.
Four competed on squats and four on large horses.
