The second place in pony jumping was taken by Amelia Pawlak, riding "Fama", and the third by Lena Boruń on "Harmider".
The youngest participant of the tournament - Inga Aksman - fought ambitiously galloping and jumping over obstacles on the small mare "Carmen".
Even greater emotions accompanied the competing amazons and spectators during the competition with the participation of large horses.
Dangerous-looking falls were scored by Paulina Szewczyk, riding "Declaration" and Anastasia Abramenko, who rode on "Lotka".
Fortunately, apart from minor bruises, neither the amazons nor the horses were hurt, so they continued to participate in the competition.
A lot of problems with introducing the young mare "Wineta" to the parkur had Weronika Łuczkiewicz riding her.
Either the assistance of a trainer or another horse was needed, followed by a little crazy "Wineta".
After completing the obstacle from the parkur she also went down in full swing, so sometimes in the pits and on the expansion room it got dangerous. "Everything is under control!" reassured Jan Sienkiewicz a little scared viewers, especially the youngest ones.
From the beginning of the big horse competition, Marta Masalska performed well on the park, riding the beautifully presented "Whisky".
This dignified mare, paired with an experienced amazon, at the second attempt in the final phase as the first to jump 135 cm and it was the best result of the competition at that moment.
After a while, however, the same height was also scored by Paulina Szewczyk on "Declaration", Weronika Łuczkiewicz on "Wineta" and Anastasia Abramenko on "Lotka".
To decorate the flo and to receive material prizes in the form of equestrian equipment, all these athletes went together, and at the end, together with the amazons on ponies, in tact of Radecki's march, they made an impressive honorary round, ending this interesting and exciting competition.
