The party's manifesto includes issues m.in the judiciary (it should be elected in general elections), tax changes (equalising the tax-free amount for all), war reparations (in the form of military aid for the countries of NATO's eastern flank, with particular emphasis on Polish), holding a referendum on the possession of weapons, limiting the number of MPs and introducing single-mandate constituencies.
A few days after the announcement of the creation of a new political formation, Mariusz Max Kolonko started talks with Marek Jakubiak.
At the end of July, Kolonko posted information on his social media profile suggesting that #R would join forces with the Kukiz'15 movement.
